</ACTION>
<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 The OCC, the Board, the FDIC and the OTS (collectively ``the agencies'') are issuing this proposed rule to implement
the portions of section 305 of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation Improvement Act of 1991 (FDICIA) that require
the agencies to revise their risk-based capital standards for insured depository institutions to ensure that those
standards take adequate account of concentration of credit risk and the risks of nontraditional activities. The
intended effect of this proposed rule is to ensure that the agencies take adequate account of concentration of credit
risk and the risks of nontraditional activities in assessing an institution's capital adequacy. The proposed rule
amends the risk-based capital standards by explicitly identifying concentration of credit risk and certain risks
arising from nontraditional activities, as well as an institution's ability to manage these risks, as important
factors in assessing an institution's overall capital adequacy. 



</SUMMARY>
