The principal persons involved in drafting this document are Walter Paskowsky, Project Manager, and LT J.M. Losego,
Project Counsel.



Background and Purpose



This bridge presently opens on signal except that from 6:15 a.m. to 7:15 a.m. and 3 p.m. to 4:30 p.m., Monday through
Friday, except federal holidays, the draw need not open. NASA, whose employees commute to and from the John F. Kennedy
Space Center across the bridge, requested a 30 minute increase in the morning closed period extending from 6 a.m. to
7:30 a.m. This change was requested to ensure continuous uninterrupted flow of highway traffic during the heaviest
daily commuter traffic periods. The bridgeowner, Brevard County, concurred with this proposal.


